28/04/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Defence Minister Ioan Mircea Pascu presented a progress report Friday (25 April), summarising structural reforms in the army for the last year. 
He said the reforms achieved a balance between continuity and structural changes aiming to improve military capabilities. 
The report cited increased participation of military troops in foreign missions, improved administrative capacity, as well as better compliance with NATO standards. 
On the downside, the document pointed out problems, including low living standards and training issues. 
(Rompres - 26/04/03)
